"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The function get_active_figure() is designed to return the current active figure, but it does not properly check if a figure is active before trying to add text to it. The ax.text() method is called on the ax object, which is not guaranteed to be associated with the active figure returned by get_active_figure(). This can lead to errors if there is no active figure.\", \"patch\": \"18c18\\n< ax.text(0.4, 0.4, \\\"Add a label to the current active figure\\\")\\n---\\n> ac_fig.text(0.4, 0.4, \\\"Add a label to the current active figure\\\")\\n\"}"